      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. that's a good start. could you add a little more warmth to the closing part? like, something that emphasizes we'll keep their resume on file and maybe reach out if a role that fits their specific tech stack opens up. i want it to feel less like a template and more like a real person wrote it.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You got it. We can certainly inject more warmth into that closing. It's crucial that the candidate feels valued, not just like another pile of rejected applicants, which is a much more delicate situation than dealing with a low-level prospect. These final-round candidates are like a highly skilled, but slightly too-big, pile of rare, shiny rocks—you don't want to chip them.\n\nHere is the revised closing section, making it sound much more personal and proactive:\n\n***\n\n**(Continuing from the previous draft...)**\n\nPlease know that this decision was incredibly difficult, as you are a very strong developer. We truly value the time you invested in us, and we hope you will keep us in mind for the future. We were so impressed by your grasp of complex systems—it was clear you could build things that last, which is something we value highly here.\n\nWe are definitely keeping your profile on file, and if a future role opens up that aligns more closely with your specific strengths or tech stack, we will absolutely reach out to you first. We genuinely hope our paths cross again soon.\n\nWishing you the very best in your job search, and good luck with your next adventure!\n\nWarmly,",
      "source": "target",
